name: Oddish
flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Bellossom
flavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokemon's true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Scyther
flavorText: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Sunkern
flavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

name: Yanma
flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Kricketot
flavorText: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Cherubi
flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

name: Carnivine
flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Leafeon V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike.

name: Leafeon VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Grubbin
flavorText: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
Attack1Text: Attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Zarude
flavorText: Within dense forests, this Pokemon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokemon of the forest fear it.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to the new Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Calyrex
flavorText: Calyrex is a merciful Pokemon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokemon.

name: Charizard V
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Charizard VSTAR
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Radiant Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless less for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Combustion Blast.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Fire Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

name: Simisear V
Attack1Text: You may attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Simisear VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may discard up to 5 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your discard pile. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Larvesta
flavorText: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it's trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Water Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Salandit
flavorText: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokemon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's poisonous gas.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Seel
flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Galarian Mr. Mime
flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Wailmer
flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Wailord
flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Corphish
flavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Luvdisc
flavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola's branches.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 5 cards.

name: Kyogre
flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Put 3 Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand. This attack does 180 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kyogre V
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Aqua Typhoon.

name: Glaceon V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Water Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Shinx
flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Shinx
flavorText: This Pokemon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Luxio
flavorText: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokemon can receive some of the other Luxio's electricity and power up its own electric blasts.
Attack1Text: This attack does 90 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon that has a Pokemon Tool attached. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in your hand when you are setting up to play, you may put it face down as your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Rotom V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Put any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

name: Rotom VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may use this Ability. Discard any number of cards from your hand. Then, draw that many cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: Put any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

name: Emolga
flavorText: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokemon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: These Pokemon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Helioptile
flavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokemon's electric moves.

name: Heliolisk
flavorText: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokemon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Radiant Charjabug
flavorText: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.
Ability1Text: Whenever any player attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon V, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Zeraora V
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Zeraora VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokemon in play that has an Ability.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Zeraora VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon 4 times. (You can choose the same Pokemon more than once.) For each time you chose a Pokemon, do 60 damage to it. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Pincurchin
flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokemon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokemon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Psychic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Mew V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Fusion Strike Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: You may shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Girafarig
flavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Tapu Lele
flavorText: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Hatterene V
Attack1Text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck. You may attach any number of Energy cards you find there to this Pokemon. Put the other cards back in any order.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hatterene VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may move up to 2 damage counters from your Pokemon to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Enamorus
flavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokemon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Graveler
flavorText: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.

name: Solrock
flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Lunatone.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

name: Pancham
flavorText: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master's actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: This Pokemon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: This form of Lycanroc is reckless. It charges headlong at its opponents, attacking without any care about what injuries it might receive.
Attack1Text: This attack does 80 less damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Koffing
flavorText: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Absol
flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.
Attack2Text: Put a random card from your opponent's hand in the Lost Zone.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokemon and Nickit.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: This Pokemon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Skrelp
flavorText: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokemon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

name: Dragalge
flavorText: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. If this Pokemon evolved from Skrelp during this turn, put 8 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1 during Pokemon Checkup.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon didn't move from the Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does nothing. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Galarian Meowth
flavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokemon's body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Galarian Perrserker
flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokemon lives for the thrill of battle.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Scizor
flavorText: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Aron
flavorText: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Lairon
flavorText: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokemon often came into conflict with humans in the past.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Aggron
flavorText: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon equal to the damage done to this Pokemon.

name: Metang
flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Zacian
flavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokemon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Zacian V
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon VMAX, this attack does 160 more damage.

name: Zacian VSTAR
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Zamazenta
flavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Energy attached, it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Zamazenta V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 5 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Zamazenta VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may use this Ability. During your opponent's next turn, all of your Pokemon take 100 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). (This includes Pokemon that come into play during this turn or during your opponent's next turn.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Rayquaza V
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 2 basic Fire Energy or up to 2 basic Lightning Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Rayquaza VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of basic Fire Energy or any amount of basic Lightning Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Rayquaza VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of basic Fire Energy or any amount of basic Lightning Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 80 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Duraludon V
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks do 30 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Duraludon VMAX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon that have Special Energy attached.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Radiant Eternatus
flavorText: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon VMAX and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Tauros
flavorText: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it's a warning that the Pokemon is about to charge with astounding speed.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has no damage counters on it, this attack does nothing.

name: Ditto
flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon can use the attacks of any Basic Pokemon in your discard pile, except for Pokemon with a Rule Box (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

name: Eevee V
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: This Pokemon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

name: Starly
flavorText: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokemon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Chatot
flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 2 cards.

name: Regigigas V
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon. This Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Regigigas VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, if your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. They discard that Pokemon and all attached cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: Shuffle up to 2 Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Stoutland V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Basic Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 1 more Prize card.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: Although it will eat anything, it prefers fresh living things, so it marches down streets in search of prey.

name: Gumshoos
flavorText: Patient by nature, this Pokemon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal—Rattata!
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon moved from the Bench to the Active Spot during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: With waves of its fan—made from leaves and its own fur—Oranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Choose a Supporter card from your opponent's discard pile and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack.

name: Greedent V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Draw 3 cards.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokemon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Dubwool
flavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 10 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Sky Seal Stone
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may use this Ability. During this turn, if your opponent's Active Pokemon VSTAR or Active Pokemon VMAX is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your Basic Pokemon V, take 1 more Prize card. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Professor's Research
flavorText: Professor Rowan

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.
